description:
File: lichen/subsys/lichen/app_identity/app_identity.c

Inconsistent validation between lichen_app_identity_set_self and lichen_app_identity_upsert_peer:

In lichen_app_identity_set_self (lines 106-109):
  if (!has_nul(identity->display_name, sizeof(identity->display_name)) ||
      !has_nul(identity->firmware_name, sizeof(identity->firmware_name))) {
      return -ENAMETOOLONG;
  }
Both display_name AND firmware_name are validated.

In lichen_app_identity_upsert_peer (lines 197-199):
  if (!has_nul(peer->display_name, sizeof(peer->display_name))) {
      return -ENAMETOOLONG;
  }
Only display_name is validated.

This is correct because lichen_app_identity_peer has no firmware_name field - only lichen_app_identity_self has it. So this is NOT a bug, just asymmetric by design.

Actually, reviewing again - this is NOT a bug. The peer struct doesn't have firmware_name. Closing as invalid.

